The Git index is a critical data structure in Git, but it can be very large in monorepos. It was a performance bottleneck for years until we found a way to shrink it: the sparse index.
Hack to avoid self-closing empty div, do not remove
Make your monorepo feel small with Git’s sparse index | The GitHub Blog
The new sparse index feature makes it feel like you are working in a small repository when working in a focused portion of a monorepo.
